	<h2>Friends of Tam</h2>

	<p>Climb Mount Tamalpais <a href="http://www.strava.com/routes/173309">via all four routes</a> in a one day.</p>

	<p>Inspired by <a href="http://www.clubcinglesventoux.org/en/club.html">The Club des Cinglés du Mont-Ventoux</a> 
		which has defined the challenge of riding Mont Ventoux three (or more) ways in a single day. Although Mt Tam 
		peaks at only half the elevation of Ventoux the route still climbs almost 14,000 feet over 85 miles.</a>
		
	<h3>The Climbs</h3>
	
	<ul>
		<li>MV: From Tam Junction in Mill Valley via Highway 1, Pantoll to East Peak</li>
		<li>SB: Stinson Beach via Pantoll to East Peak</li>
		<li>BF: BoFax to Ridgecrest and East Peak</li>
		<li>FF: Fairfax to Alpine Dam, Ridgecrest and East Peak</li>
	</ul>

